          <p>The following accepted conditions are listed on your DVA Health Card:</p>

          <section class="widget">
            <div class="row widget-content widget--justclaims">
              <div class="col-md-12">
                <table class="table-claims">
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <p class="status-icon status-approved">
                        Lumbar Spondylosis
                        <br />
                        <span>Approved
                          <em>&ndash; 06 Feb 2018</em>
                        </span>
                      </p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <p class="status-icon status-approved">
                        Mental Health Treatment (NLHC)
                        <br />
                        <span>Approved

                        </span>
                      </p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>

        <div class="container margin-below--extra">
          <section>
            <h2>
              <span class="font-weight-heavy">Lost, stolen or damaged cards</span>
            </h2>
            <p>A replacement card can be issues if your card is lost, stolen or damaged. Your card number will remain the same but the expiration date will be updated.</p>
            <!-- <p>It may take up to four weeks for a new card to be issued. In the meantime, you can use your original letter of authority for this period, or your health provider may phone
              DVA for information about your eligibility and entitlements.</p> -->
            <button class="uikit-btn uikit-btn--tertiary" onclick="window.location.href='/healthcard-replacement'">Request a replacement card</button>
          </section>
        </div>

      </main>
